  "text": "Polymer (Oxidized State) + M + + e − ↔ Polymer (Reduced State), where M + represents cation and e − represents electron [CITATION_1] . The decrease in conductivity has also been interpreted in terms of an ion-leveraged mechanism, where the disorder driven metal-insulator-transition is characterized by charge localization which is controlled by the ionic environment [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This model interprets the slow response to the percolation of the ions from the electrolyte into the organic film, under the influence of the vertical electric field, affecting the conductance of PEDOT:PSS [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
